The paper deals with decentralized hypothesis testing in a wireless sensor network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of energy harvesting sensors and the queuing-theoretic model for the battery suggest a focus on control systems (cs.SY) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA). Finally, the design and optimization of sensor networks with energy harvesting sensors may fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
